well, I see you are still listed as part of the TAG, so may be in a
position of influence.

I will take Stuart Williams aside the next time I see him at the
coffee machine and express my disappointment on the process. I have
already expressed some deep unhappiness about the way that WS-A got to
1.0 without any tests, which is the complete anathema of develoment
from a test centric viewpoint (if your standard has no tests, how do
you assess compliance?), but left with the impression that the TAG
views testing as an implementation detail, not a better way to
describe specifications: a formal description you can code against.

-steve

